{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7Er1LX1W7zuavGxhfL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. Tests pass.\n\n**Root cause:** In `src/userService.js`, the cache key was `users:${opts.team}` — it ignored `opts.includeArchived`. So a call that requested a team *with* archived users cached the full list under that team's key, and the picker's next call for the same team (which requests only active users) got a cache hit and received the archived users too. The TTL is 60s, which is why refreshing after a minute clears it.\n\n**Fix:** Include `includeArchived` in the cache key so active and archived requests are cached separately:\n```js\nconst key = `users:${opts.team}:${opts.includeArchived ? \"all\" : \"active\"}`;\n```\n\nNote: the existing test suite (`test/`) covers only `cache.js` — there's no test exercising `getUsers`, so `npm test` passing doesn't directly assert this fix. Want me to add a regression test for the cache-key leak?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":312,"cache_read_input_tokens":22310,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":312},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ee9c7297-1cfb-403f-9ca6-ba6f0396a99a","uuid":"9e7e1ff9-7079-4305-8bd6-16947fad0b3c","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:37:54.790Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7EocUbLepdSHv4HaBv"}
